aiCLC.description: The MIB Module for Series 1 Common Logic Controllers (CLC)

aiCLCBox1DensAdmin.name: aiCLCBox1DensAdmin
aiCLCBox1DensAdmin.description: The administration value for the slot density for Chassis 1 of and AISwitch.

aiCLCBox2DensAdmin.name: aiCLCBox2DensAdmin
aiCLCBox2DensAdmin.description: The administration value for the slot density for Chassis 2 of and AISwitch.

aiCLCBox3DensAdmin.name: aiCLCBox3DensAdmin
aiCLCBox3DensAdmin.description: The administration value for the slot density for Chassis 3 of and AISwitch.

aiCLCBox4DensAdmin.name: aiCLCBox4DensAdmin
aiCLCBox4DensAdmin.description: The administration value for the slot density for Chassis 4 of and AISwitch.

aiCLCBox5DensAdmin.name: aiCLCBox5DensAdmin
aiCLCBox5DensAdmin.description: The administration value for the slot density for Chassis 5 of and AISwitch.

aiCLCBox6DensAdmin.name: aiCLCBox6DensAdmin
aiCLCBox6DensAdmin.description: The administration value for the slot density for Chassis 6 of and AISwitch.

aiCLCBox7DensAdmin.name: aiCLCBox7DensAdmin
aiCLCBox7DensAdmin.description: The administration value for the slot density for Chassis 7 of and AISwitch.

aiCLCBox8DensAdmin.name: aiCLCBox8DensAdmin
aiCLCBox8DensAdmin.description: The administration value for the slot density for Chassis 8 of and AISwitch.

aiCLCNodeName.name: aiCLCNodeName
aiCLCNodeName.description: This associates a name with an AI Switch. This string is part of the prompt for a user port.

aiCLCLogPortEnable.name: aiCLCLogPortEnable
aiCLCLogPortEnable.description: Enable/Disable the display of Alarm and Activity Information.

aiCLCAlmLogPort.name: aiCLCAlmLogPort
aiCLCAlmLogPort.description: The Alarm and Activity Log Port Number.

aiCLCActLogLvl.name: aiCLCActLogLvl
aiCLCActLogLvl.description: The alarm level which when met or exceeded will cause messages to be printed on the log port.

aiCLCMinorAlmMin.name: aiCLCMinorAlmMin
aiCLCMinorAlmMin.description: The alarm level which when met or exceeded will cause a minor alarm to be reported.

aiCLCMinorAlmMax.name: aiCLCMinorAlmMax
aiCLCMinorAlmMax.description: The alarm level which when exceeded will not cause a minor alarm to be reported.

aiCLCMajorAlmMin.name: aiCLCMajorAlmMin
aiCLCMajorAlmMin.description: The alarm level which when met or exceeded will cause a major alarm to be reported.

aiCLCMajorAlmMax.name: aiCLCMajorAlmMax
aiCLCMajorAlmMax.description: The alarm level which when exceeded will not cause a major alarm to be reported.

aiCLCCraftLogEcho.name: aiCLCCraftLogEcho
aiCLCCraftLogEcho.description: Echo Alarm and Activity information on the craft port.

aiCLCCaamlRoute.name: aiCLCCaamlRoute
aiCLCCaamlRoute.description: Name of the destination used for the CAAML Log.

aiCLCCaamlIdleTmr.name: aiCLCCaamlIdleTmr
aiCLCCaamlIdleTmr.description: The number of seconds that must pass without any messages being printed on CAAML, before the CAAML connection is torn down.

aiCLCCaamlRetryTmr.name: aiCLCCaamlRetryTmr
aiCLCCaamlRetryTmr.description: The number of seconds that must pass after an unsuccessful attempt at bringing the CAAML connection up before a retry will occur.

aiCLCConnInfo.name: aiCLCConnInfo
aiCLCConnInfo.description: Print connection information on user terminals.

aiCLCLongBrkLen.name: aiCLCLongBrkLen
aiCLCLongBrkLen.description: Long Break length in milliseconds rounded to the nearest 1/64th second.

aiCLCDestMenu.name: aiCLCDestMenu
aiCLCDestMenu.description: Print Destination Menu on user terminals.

aiCLCDownSpd.name: aiCLCDownSpd
aiCLCDownSpd.description: Allow ports of different speeds to be connected.

aiCLCFaultSwitch.name: aiCLCFaultSwitch
aiCLCFaultSwitch.description: In dual CLC systems, a fault on the active CLC will cause automatic switchover from the faulted CLC to the backup CLC.

aiCLCDestMenuFmt.name: aiCLCDestMenuFmt
aiCLCDestMenuFmt.description: The number of columns used to print the destination menu.

aiCLCAutoCLCUpdate.name: aiCLCAutoCLCUpdate
aiCLCAutoCLCUpdate.description: Automatic configuration of the backup CLC when the active CLC's configuration changes.

aiCLCAlarmLvl.name: aiCLCAlarmLvl
aiCLCAlarmLvl.description: Current Alarm Level. A write clears the alarms. A read returns the current alarm level.

aiCLCTimeDate.name: aiCLCTimeDate
aiCLCTimeDate.description: This is the Current Time and Date. The DateAndTime type is a structured OCTET STRING, defined in v2-tc.my (SNMPv2 Textual Conventions).

aiCLCRstTimeDate.name: aiCLCRstTimeDate
aiCLCRstTimeDate.description: This is the Time and Date of Last Reset. The DateAndTime type is a structured OCTET STRING, defined in v2-tc.my (SNMPv2 Textual Conventions).

aiCLCHoldConn.name: aiCLCHoldConn
aiCLCHoldConn.description: Number of connections placed on hold

aiCLCQueuedPorts.name: aiCLCQueuedPorts
aiCLCQueuedPorts.description: Number of ports in wait queue

aiCLCVersion.name: aiCLCVersion
aiCLCVersion.description: Software version, time, and date of currently executing software

aiCLCCpu.name: aiCLCCpu
aiCLCCpu.description: The location of the active CLC.

aiCLCCpyConfig.name: aiCLCCpyConfig
aiCLCCpyConfig.description: Copy configuration from active CLC to backup CLC. A write of copy(2) causes the transfer to begin. A read will return copy(2) if a transfer is in progress and a none(1) if idle. A write of none(1) is not permitted and is flagged as an error.

aiCLCDLWinIn.name: aiCLCDLWinIn
aiCLCDLWinIn.description: Verbose report of incoming Window Transactions.

aiCLCDLWinOut.name: aiCLCDLWinOut
aiCLCDLWinOut.description: Verbose report of outgoing Window Transactions.

aiCLCDLWinUni.name: aiCLCDLWinUni
aiCLCDLWinUni.description: Verbose report of unified Window Transactions.

aiCLCDebugVal.name: aiCLCDebugVal
aiCLCDebugVal.description: Value of the debug variable representing all debug combinations.

aiCLCSwitchRestart.name: aiCLCSwitchRestart
aiCLCSwitchRestart.description: A write of this object causes the switch to be restarted in the designated mode. A read of this object always returns the value restart(1), which has no particular significance.

aiCLCInitStrings.name: aiCLCInitStrings
aiCLCInitStrings.description: This object is used to test the condition of the strings on the CLC. A read of this object causes the test to be performed and then reports the outcome.

aiCLCCopyFlash.name: aiCLCCopyFlash
aiCLCCopyFlash.description: Copy Flash from one bank to another. AP - Active Primary AS - Active Secondary BP - Backup Primary BS - Backup Secondary A read returns a value corresponding to the activity in progress. A write causes the requested transfer to begin. A write of none(1) is not permitted and is flagged as an error.

aiCLCCopyFlashToSLC.name: aiCLCCopyFlashToSLC
aiCLCCopyFlashToSLC.description: This object is used to begin or obtain the status of the SLC Download process. Writing a SLC base port to this object will cause the SLC at that baseport to search for new firmware on the active or backup CLC. If a valid SLC image is located, then the SLC will download that code and begin to run. A read of this variable will return the value 1 if a SLC download is in process, or a 0 if there aren't downloads in progress.

aiCLCReadCommunity.name: aiCLCReadCommunity
aiCLCReadCommunity.description: The read community string for the CLC.

aiCLCWriteCommunity.name: aiCLCWriteCommunity
aiCLCWriteCommunity.description: The write community string for the CLC.

aiCLCIPAdrs.name: aiCLCIPAdrs
aiCLCIPAdrs.description: The IP address for the CLC.

aiCLCRouterIPAdrs.name: aiCLCRouterIPAdrs
aiCLCRouterIPAdrs.description: The router ip address for the CLC.

aiCLCSubnetIPAdrs.name: aiCLCSubnetIPAdrs
aiCLCSubnetIPAdrs.description: The subnet mask for the CLC.

aiCLCTrapTable.name: aiCLCTrapTable
aiCLCTrapTable.description: A table of Trap destination IP addresses.

aiCLCLastTrapMsgText.name: aiCLCLastTrapMsgText
aiCLCLastTrapMsgText.description: This is the message text associated with the last generated trap.

aiCLCLastTrapMsgNum.name: aiCLCLastTrapMsgNum
aiCLCLastTrapMsgNum.description: This is the message number of the last generated trap log message.

aiCLCCrashMsgText.name: aiCLCCrashMsgText
aiCLCCrashMsgText.description: This is a place holder. It is required to allow verification of OID of trap crash message object. A read of this object will return an empty string.

aiCLCNumEventsSinceLastTrap.name: aiCLCNumEventsSinceLastTrap
aiCLCNumEventsSinceLastTrap.description: This is the number of times an event that would generate a trap has occurred since the last time that trap was transmitted. The traps are not transmitted while the aiCLCTrapTimer is running. This number will accompany the next transmitted trap. This object is really a place holder. It is required to allow verification of the OID of this information in a trap (var-bind). A read of this object will result in an error from the snmp agent.

aiCLCTrapTimer.name: aiCLCTrapTimer
aiCLCTrapTimer.description: After a trap is generated, a timer is started. If the event that generated the trap occurs while the timer is running, no trap will be generated for the event. The value of this object is the duration of the timer in SECONDS.

aiCLCAsyncTrap.name: aiCLCAsyncTrap
aiCLCAsyncTrap.description: When this object is enabled, link up/link down traps are sent to managers listed in the trap table. The traps are normally not used and must specifically be enabled by a manager.

aiCLCTelnetServerPort.name: aiCLCTelnetServerPort
aiCLCTelnetServerPort.description: The tcp port number used by the telnet server may be configured using the aiCLCTelnetServerPort object. By default this object uses the well known port number 23.

aiCLCColdStartTrapDelay.name: aiCLCColdStartTrapDelay
aiCLCColdStartTrapDelay.description: The sending of the cold start trap may be delayed to allow system startup and link startup to occur. This will typically be done on systems using IP over X.25 links. This value is specified in seconds.

aiCLCFtpCtrlPort.name: aiCLCFtpCtrlPort
aiCLCFtpCtrlPort.description: The FTP Server control port number. New values for this object take affect after a reset. The FTP Server data port is automatically selected to be one less than the control port.

aiCLCBackupCLCHealth.name: aiCLCBackupCLCHealth
aiCLCBackupCLCHealth.description: Health status of the Backup CLC.

aiCLCBanner.name: aiCLCBanner
aiCLCBanner.description: The banner for the CLC. There is a maximum 15 lines with 76 characters allowed per line.

aiCLCTimeZone.name: aiCLCTimeZone
aiCLCTimeZone.description: The time zone offset for the CLC in minutes.

aiCLCSNTPPrimaryServer.name: aiCLCSNTPPrimaryServer
aiCLCSNTPPrimaryServer.description: The IP address for the Primary SNTP Server.

aiCLCSNTPSecondaryServer.name: aiCLCSNTPSecondaryServer
aiCLCSNTPSecondaryServer.description: The IP address for the Secondary SNTP Server.

aiCLCRadiusAddr1.name: aiCLCRadiusAddr1
aiCLCRadiusAddr1.description: The IP address for the Primary RADIUS Server.

aiCLCRadiusPort1.name: aiCLCRadiusPort1
aiCLCRadiusPort1.description: The port number associated with the Primary RADIUS Server.

aiCLCRadiusSecret1.name: aiCLCRadiusSecret1
aiCLCRadiusSecret1.description: The Secret for the Primary RADIUS Server.

aiCLCRadiusAddr2.name: aiCLCRadiusAddr2
aiCLCRadiusAddr2.description: The IP address for the Secondary RADIUS Server.

aiCLCRadiusPort2.name: aiCLCRadiusPort2
aiCLCRadiusPort2.description: The port number associated with the Secondary RADIUS Server.

aiCLCRadiusSecret2.name: aiCLCRadiusSecret2
aiCLCRadiusSecret2.description: The Secret for the Secondary RADIUS Server.

aiCLCTrapInterval.name: aiCLCTrapInterval
aiCLCTrapInterval.description: The interval of the faulted primary CLC trap. If the primary CLC was faulted and the interval was set between 1 and 65535 minutes, the backup CLC will repeatedly send the faulted primary CLC trap. To disable this trap, set the interval to 0. If reset the interval to 0 after the primary CLC has been faulted, the backup CLC will stop sending the trap. New value for this object will take affect without rebooting the switch. This object has no effect on other traps.

aiCLCTacacsAddr1.name: aiCLCTacacsAddr1
aiCLCTacacsAddr1.description: The IP address for the Primary TACACS Server.

aiCLCTacacsPort1.name: aiCLCTacacsPort1
aiCLCTacacsPort1.description: The port number associated with the Primary TACACS Server.

aiCLCTacacsSecret1.name: aiCLCTacacsSecret1
aiCLCTacacsSecret1.description: The Secret for the Primary TACACS Server.

aiCLCTacacsAddr2.name: aiCLCTacacsAddr2
aiCLCTacacsAddr2.description: The IP address for the Secondary TACACS Server.

aiCLCTacacsPort2.name: aiCLCTacacsPort2
aiCLCTacacsPort2.description: The port number associated with the Secondary TACACS Server.

aiCLCTacacsSecret2.name: aiCLCTacacsSecret2
aiCLCTacacsSecret2.description: The Secret for the Secondary TACACS Server.

aiCLCTrapTableEntry.name: aiCLCTrapTableEntry
aiCLCTrapTableEntry.description: Information about a particular Trap destination.

aiCLCTrapIPAdrs.name: aiCLCTrapIPAdrs
aiCLCTrapIPAdrs.description: The IP Address of the destination to which SNMP Traps will be sent.

aiCLCTrapRowStatus.name: aiCLCTrapRowStatus
aiCLCTrapRowStatus.description: The aiCLC Trap Table entry row status.

aiCLCCardTable.name: aiCLCCardTable
aiCLCCardTable.description: A table of line cards contained in an AISwitch.

aiCLCCardTableEntry.name: aiCLCCardTableEntry
aiCLCCardTableEntry.description: Information about a particular line card.

aiCLCCTAdminStatus.name: aiCLCCTAdminStatus
aiCLCCTAdminStatus.description: This represents the state of the card and may be used to change the state of the card. For DUMB cards if one port on the card is up, then the entire card is considered to be up.

aiCLCCTBasePort.name: aiCLCCTBasePort
aiCLCCTBasePort.description: The base port number for the line card.

aiCLCCTHighPort.name: aiCLCCTHighPort
aiCLCCTHighPort.description: The highest port number accessible by the line card.

aiCLCCTRdCommStr.name: aiCLCCTRdCommStr
aiCLCCTRdCommStr.description: The SNMP read community string by which this card is known.

aiCLCCTWrCommStr.name: aiCLCCTWrCommStr
aiCLCCTWrCommStr.description: The SNMP write community string by which this card is known.

aiCLCCTCardSnmpState.name: aiCLCCTCardSnmpState
aiCLCCTCardSnmpState.description: This field describes the capabilities of the card. A card may not be snmp capable and will have the value nosnmp(1). A card may be snmp capable but isn't present on the IP network. This card is may proxied for and will have the type snmpProxy(2). The last type of snmp capability is where are card is present on the IP network and can be managed directly. This card will have a type of snmpDirect(3).

aiCLCCTSlotExp.name: aiCLCCTSlotExp
aiCLCCTSlotExp.description: The number of slots the line card is to logically occupy.

aiCLCCTIPAdrs.name: aiCLCCTIPAdrs
aiCLCCTIPAdrs.description: The IP address associated with the line card.

aiCLCCTRtrIPAdrs.name: aiCLCCTRtrIPAdrs
aiCLCCTRtrIPAdrs.description: The router ip address for this line card.

aiCLCCTSubnetMask.name: aiCLCCTSubnetMask
aiCLCCTSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask for this line card.

aiCLCCTAutoIdIndex.name: aiCLCCTAutoIdIndex
aiCLCCTAutoIdIndex.description: The index into the Auto Id table associated with this line card.

aiCLCCTSysOID.name: aiCLCCTSysOID
aiCLCCTSysOID.description: The SNMP System OID associated with this line card.

aiCLCCTIPRange.name: aiCLCCTIPRange
aiCLCCTIPRange.description: The IP address range of this line card.

aiCLCCTTelnetPort.name: aiCLCCTTelnetPort
aiCLCCTTelnetPort.description: The telnet port of this line card.

aiCLCCTCardReset.name: aiCLCCTCardReset
aiCLCCTCardReset.description: Card is included when * is used with STPSLC, DISABL, or ENABL.

aiCLCCTLastSequenceNumber.name: aiCLCCTLastSequenceNumber
aiCLCCTLastSequenceNumber.description: This is the sequence number of the last trap sent by this card. The sequence number starts at zero following a hardware reset or power-up. When the sequence number reaches 0xffffffff, it rolls over to 0 on the next trap.

aiCLCCTRtr2IPAdrs.name: aiCLCCTRtr2IPAdrs
aiCLCCTRtr2IPAdrs.description: The secondary router ip address for this line card.

aiCLCPortTableEntry.name: aiCLCPortTableEntry
aiCLCPortTableEntry.description: Information unique to a particular port.

aiCLCPortNumber.name: aiCLCPortNumber
aiCLCPortNumber.description: The AISwitch Port Number associated with the entry.

aiCLCPortType.name: aiCLCPortType
aiCLCPortType.description: This is used to configure how the port is being used.

aiCLCPortDedicated.name: aiCLCPortDedicated
aiCLCPortDedicated.description: The port number to which this port is dedicated when the type is 'dedicated'.

aiCLCPortDestName.name: aiCLCPortDestName
aiCLCPortDestName.description: The destination to which this port is assigned.

aiCLCPortEcho.name: aiCLCPortEcho
aiCLCPortEcho.description: This determines whether echoing is on when the port is connected to the AISwitch.

aiCLCPortDestMenu.name: aiCLCPortDestMenu
aiCLCPortDestMenu.description: This determines whether the destination menu is displayed when the port type is 'user'.

aiCLCPortQueue.name: aiCLCPortQueue
aiCLCPortQueue.description: This determines whether the port is allowed to be put on hold when the destination port is busy.

aiCLCSLCProtocolCode.name: aiCLCSLCProtocolCode
aiCLCSLCProtocolCode.description: This is the slc protocol processing code.

aiCLCPortState.name: aiCLCPortState
aiCLCPortState.description: This is used to determine whether the port is enabled or disabled.

aiCLCPortStatus.name: aiCLCPortStatus
aiCLCPortStatus.description: This value is the port status which include the following values; idle(1), selecting class of service selcos(2), entering password pswd(3), entering username(4), entering destination network address dna(5), entering a TCP address tcp(6), answering 'wish to queue' queue(7), answering 'wish to hold' holdq(8), connected to switch ai(9), connected conn(10), in the process of connecting preconn(11), in the process of disconnecting predisc(12), hold(13), network connect pending netconn(14), performing a file transfer file(15), inactive inact(16), slc is receiving software download swdwn(17), port is using a telnet client telnetClient(18), unknown(20).

aiCLCPortAlm.name: aiCLCPortAlm
aiCLCPortAlm.description: The current alarm value for the port.

aiCLCPortDesc.name: aiCLCPortDesc
aiCLCPortDesc.description: This is used to describe the port in textual form.

aiCLCPortReset.name: aiCLCPortReset
aiCLCPortReset.description: Port is included when * is used with DISABL or ENABL.

aiCLCAliasTable.name: aiCLCAliasTable
aiCLCAliasTable.description: A table of call alias information.

aiCLCAliasTableEntry.name: aiCLCAliasTableEntry
aiCLCAliasTableEntry.description: Information unique to a particular alias.

aiCLCAliasIndex.name: aiCLCAliasIndex
aiCLCAliasIndex.description: The alias name in the form of a DisplayString. This is the key field for the Alias Table.

aiCLCAliasRowStatus.name: aiCLCAliasRowStatus
aiCLCAliasRowStatus.description: The Alias Table Entry row status.

aiCLCXlatType.name: aiCLCXlatType
aiCLCXlatType.description: The type of alias translation to be performed.

aiCLCAliasDestName.name: aiCLCAliasDestName
aiCLCAliasDestName.description: The destination to be used for the alias.

aiCLCCalledAdrs.name: aiCLCCalledAdrs
aiCLCCalledAdrs.description: The called address used in the macro.

aiCLCAliasDestMenu.name: aiCLCAliasDestMenu
aiCLCAliasDestMenu.description: This determines whether the alias appears on the destination menu.

aiCLCLinkNum.name: aiCLCLinkNum
aiCLCLinkNum.description: The link number or alias macro used for the link number.

aiCLCCallerAdrs.name: aiCLCCallerAdrs
aiCLCCallerAdrs.description: The caller address used in the macro.

aiCLCCallData.name: aiCLCCallData
aiCLCCallData.description: The call data which may be a destination or an alias macro.

aiCLCApplicString.name: aiCLCApplicString
aiCLCApplicString.description: The application string which may be a string or an alias macro.

aiCLCCalledProtoStr.name: aiCLCCalledProtoStr
aiCLCCalledProtoStr.description: The string that may specify the called protocol for a call using the alias macro.

aiCLCCallerProtoStr.name: aiCLCCallerProtoStr
aiCLCCallerProtoStr.description: The string that may specify the calling protocol for a call using the alias macro.

aiCLCAlternRoute.name: aiCLCAlternRoute
aiCLCAlternRoute.description: The string may specify a destination or an alias macro that is used as an alternate route.

aiCLCAliasPosition.name: aiCLCAliasPosition
aiCLCAliasPosition.description: The position of the alias in the alias list. When 'set' a new or an existing alias, this value can be used as a flag to request a saving to the beginning (0) or to the end (99999) of the alias list. As default, the CLC always saves a new alias to the end and a modified alias to its old position.

aiCLCDestTable.name: aiCLCDestTable
aiCLCDestTable.description: This table contains information pertaining to destinations and their attributes.

aiCLCDestTableEntry.name: aiCLCDestTableEntry
aiCLCDestTableEntry.description: This information pertains to one entry in the destination table.

aiCLCDestName.name: aiCLCDestName
aiCLCDestName.description: The name of the destination in the form of an OCTET STRING.

aiCLCDestRowStatus.name: aiCLCDestRowStatus
aiCLCDestRowStatus.description: The key field for the Destination table entry.

aiCLCDestCallInit.name: aiCLCDestCallInit
aiCLCDestCallInit.description: This is used to turn on or turn off call initiation on ports assigned to this destination.

aiCLCDestDisc.name: aiCLCDestDisc
aiCLCDestDisc.description: This is used to turn on or turn off the user's disconnect keys when connected to this destination.

aiCLCDestDispMenu.name: aiCLCDestDispMenu
aiCLCDestDispMenu.description: This is used to turn on or turn off the display of the destination name on the destination menu.

aiCLCDestBaud.name: aiCLCDestBaud
aiCLCDestBaud.description: This is used to turn on or turn off whether the baud rate is checked before connecting to the destination.

aiCLCDestIsSwitch.name: aiCLCDestIsSwitch
aiCLCDestIsSwitch.description: This is used to indicate that the destination is another AI switch.

aiCLCDestTmrType.name: aiCLCDestTmrType
aiCLCDestTmrType.description: This is used to set the type of timer associated with the destination.

aiCLCDestTmrVal.name: aiCLCDestTmrVal
aiCLCDestTmrVal.description: This value is the timer duration in milliseconds ranging from 1mS to 4368000mS or about 72 hours.

aiCLCDestTmrDelay.name: aiCLCDestTmrDelay
aiCLCDestTmrDelay.description: This value is the delay in milliseconds before allowing further calls on the destination after a call terminates. The range is 1mS to 4368000mS or about 72 hours.

aiCLCDestPswd.name: aiCLCDestPswd
aiCLCDestPswd.description: This is password associated with the destination.

aiCLCDestQPswd.name: aiCLCDestQPswd
aiCLCDestQPswd.description: This is password used to control access to the queue management functions associated with the destination.

aiCLCDestMenuMsg.name: aiCLCDestMenuMsg
aiCLCDestMenuMsg.description: This string is displayed next to the destination in the destination menu.

aiCLCDestConnMsg.name: aiCLCDestConnMsg
aiCLCDestConnMsg.description: This string is forced out the destination port when a connection begins.

aiCLCDestDiscMsg.name: aiCLCDestDiscMsg
aiCLCDestDiscMsg.description: This string is forced out the destination port when a connection terminates.

aiCLCDestState.name: aiCLCDestState
aiCLCDestState.description: This is used to enable or disable the destination.

aiCLCDestNumPorts.name: aiCLCDestNumPorts
aiCLCDestNumPorts.description: This is used to determine the number of ports assigned to this destination.

aiCLCDestNumUsed.name: aiCLCDestNumUsed
aiCLCDestNumUsed.description: This is used to determine the number of ports in use for this destination.

aiCLCDestNumFree.name: aiCLCDestNumFree
aiCLCDestNumFree.description: This is used to determine the number of ports that are free for this destination.

aiCLCDestQHigh.name: aiCLCDestQHigh
aiCLCDestQHigh.description: This is used to determine the maximum number of ports that were queued to this destination.

aiCLCDestPortList.name: aiCLCDestPortList
aiCLCDestPortList.description: This string contains a list of port numbers assigned to this destination.

aiCLCDestWaitForPort.name: aiCLCDestWaitForPort
aiCLCDestWaitForPort.description: This is used to allow the user to wait for a port when all ports for the destination are busy.

aiCLCAsyncifIndex.name: aiCLCAsyncifIndex
aiCLCAsyncifIndex.description: The ifIndex from the interfaces table.

aiCLCAsyncAdminStatus.name: aiCLCAsyncAdminStatus
aiCLCAsyncAdminStatus.description: The key field for the Async table entry.

aiCLCAsyncDiscType.name: aiCLCAsyncDiscType
aiCLCAsyncDiscType.description: The disconnect type for the async port.

aiCLCEIASignals.name: aiCLCEIASignals
aiCLCEIASignals.description: The EIA signals may be disabled (eiaDisabled(1)) or configured for pass through (dsrRtsPass(2)). Additionally the port can be configured to disconnect on loss of DSR (dsrOffDisc(3)), disconnect on change of state of DSR (dsrOnOffDisc(4)), disconnect on loss of DCD (dcdOffDisc(5)), or disconnect on change of state of DCD (dcdOnOffDisc(6)).

aiCLCEIARtsDisc.name: aiCLCEIARtsDisc
aiCLCEIARtsDisc.description: Upon disconnect RTS may be configured to be on(1), or off(2).

aiCLCEIADtrDisc.name: aiCLCEIADtrDisc
aiCLCEIADtrDisc.description: Upon disconnect DTR may be configured to be on(1), or off(2).

aiCLCEIARtsConn.name: aiCLCEIARtsConn
aiCLCEIARtsConn.description: Upon connect RTS may be configured to be on(1), or off(2).

aiCLCEIADtrConn.name: aiCLCEIADtrConn
aiCLCEIADtrConn.description: Upon connect DTR may be configured to be on(1), or off(2).

aiCLCEIARtsToggle.name: aiCLCEIARtsToggle
aiCLCEIARtsToggle.description: Upon disconnect RTS may be configured to toggle (on(1)) or not (off(2)).

aiCLCEIADtrToggle.name: aiCLCEIADtrToggle
aiCLCEIADtrToggle.description: Upon disconnect DTR may be configured to toggle (on(1)) or not (off(2)).

aiCLCAutoIDTable.name: aiCLCAutoIDTable
aiCLCAutoIDTable.description: A table of board identification information for an AISwitch.

aiCLCAutoIDTableEntry.name: aiCLCAutoIDTableEntry
aiCLCAutoIDTableEntry.description: Board Identification information for a particular card.

aiCLCAIDPort.name: aiCLCAIDPort
aiCLCAIDPort.description: The port number where the card resides. If the port number is not valid then 256 will be reported.

aiCLCAIDProduct.name: aiCLCAIDProduct
aiCLCAIDProduct.description: The product name for the card.

aiCLCAIDSerialNumber.name: aiCLCAIDSerialNumber
